## 1. Float64, univariate — the Cella core (HR132 / HR133 / HR134)

### 1.1 The rational-op class — exact account in ℚ

| Operation | Account it carries | Status |
|---|---|---|
| `add`, `sub` | exact rounding residue (error-free transform) | DEMONSTRATED |
| `mul` | exact rounding residue | DEMONSTRATED |
| `div` | exact residue; typed refusal at poles | DEMONSTRATED |
| `pow` (integer exponent) | exact residue via repeated mul | DEMONSTRATED |
| `neg`, `abs` | exact (no rounding) | DEMONSTRATED |
| `sqrt` | certified route into the rational class (Sterbenz / EFT regime) | DEMONSTRATED |

**Scope.** Float value + residue lanes equal the true real answer
*exactly in ℚ*, universally on the tested battery. The account is
lawful under precision doubling (the Refinement Law, certified over
120,096 steps), supports an exact difference/derivative tower (every
Taylor coefficient recovered exactly by falling-factorial inversion),
and certifies root-closure objects (the atlas, HR135).

**Limitations.**
- Exactness is **class-scoped**: it holds only for operations whose
  exact result is rational given rational inputs. Step outside the
  class and the guarantee weakens to enclosure-or-refusal (§1.2).
- **Univariate** at the certification layer (the lift to several
  variables is §3, a separate substrate).
- `div` refuses (`pole`) at a zero denominator rather than emitting.
- Source: `evals/bigraded_jet.py`, `evals/difference_tower/`
  (`RATIONAL_OPS`); HR132/133/134.

### 1.2 The certified elementary annex — enclosure-or-refusal

`sqrt`, `log`, `log2`, `exp`, `pow` (general real), `sin`, `cos`,
`tan`, `atan`, `asin`, `acos`.

**Scope.** Correctly-rounded-or-honest-refusal per value, on the
`typed_refine` kernel: working precision is raised until both
enclosure ends round to the same p-bit value, else a typed refusal.

**Limitations.**
- These operations **break rationality**, so they get a certified
  **enclosure**, *not* an exact ℚ account. Correctness is
  unconditional per value; *totality* is budget-relative (Axiom 3) —
  the honest failure mode is `REFINED_BUDGET_EXCEEDED` /
  `REFINED_DOMAIN_REFUSED`, never a silent guess.
- Source: `observers/typed_*.py`; HR123–128 lineage.

