## 4. One-screen summary

| Substrate | Operations | Account closes in ℚ? | Hard limits |
|---|---|---|---|
| Float64 univariate (rational class) | `+ − × ÷`, int `pow`, `neg`, `abs`, `sqrt`-route | **Yes, exact** | class-scoped; univariate; `÷` refuses at poles |
| Float64 elementary annex | `sqrt log log2 exp pow sin cos tan atan asin acos` | No — certified **enclosure** | budget-relative totality; refusal not guess |
| Integer / bitwise (w∈{32,64}) | `add sub mul` (wrap), `shl shr`, `divmod×3 semantics`, `cast×2`, `bitcast` | **Yes, exact** | widths 32/64; FISR demo-tier; no G-claims |
| Multivariate (x,y,z; n≤3) | `add sub mul div neg abs pow(n≥1) max` | **Yes, exact** | n≤3; frozen fixtures; no invariants; kink/pole refusals |

**The boundaries deliberately *not* crossed** (fenced, not failed):
substrate promotion to released primitives (F13); n > 3 variables;
integer widths beyond 32/64; anything in G / cross-fixture-invariant
territory (F8/F9); transcendental *exactness* (the annex stays
enclosure-or-refusal by the nature of the operations).

